<task id="R7-094" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire Library modal into spaarke-ai chat surface (FR-18)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>9</wave>
    <estimated-effort>3-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>code-page, ui, wave-9</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>093</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-18 (consumer surface 1 of 3)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the Playbook Library modal into the spaarke-ai chat surface (src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/).
    Add a "Browse Playbooks" affordance at the mount point recommended by task 093's audit. When
    clicked, the affordance opens the PlaybookLibraryShell modal. The modal lists every playbook
    with its consumer mapping. Clicking a playbook invokes it through proper Path A.5 routing
    (consumer code -> IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync -> IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync).
    Reuse the shared PlaybookLibraryShell component — do not duplicate its UI.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React / Fluent UI v9 developer familiar with the spaarke-ai code page (Spaarke.UI.Components,
    @spaarke/auth, Path A.5 dispatch). Reuse over invention.
  </role>

  <goal>
    spaarke-ai chat surface now has a "Browse Playbooks" affordance such that:
    1. Affordance mounted at the location task 093 audit recommended (e.g., ConversationPane toolbar,
       CommandHelpPanel, or WelcomePanel — pick the recommended candidate).
    2. Affordance triggers a modal Dialog wrapping PlaybookLibraryShell (the shared component from
       Spaarke.UI.Components). Modal opens; modal closes on cancel/backdrop.
    3. Modal lists every playbook with its consumer mapping (consumer code visible per row).
    4. Clicking a playbook invokes it through Path A.5 routing — verified by inspecting BFF log
       or behavioral check (the invocation must NOT bypass IConsumerRoutingService /
       IInvokePlaybookAi).
    5. Affordance follows ADR-021 (dark-mode-compliant semantic tokens; no hardcoded colors).
    6. Component test added at src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/__tests__/PlaybookLibraryAffordance.test.tsx
       (or equivalent — mirror existing __tests__ pattern in same dir) confirming affordance opens
       modal + selection callback fires.
    7. No new app-level state management library introduced (use existing pattern in the code page).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="audit-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="shared-modal-component">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="spaarke-ai-app">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="spaarke-ai-conversation">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="spaarke-ai-welcome">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/CommandHelpPanel.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — playbook launch from modal MUST flow through IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (Path A.5). NO direct PlaybookOrchestrationService call, NO bypass.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021 (referenced)">Dark mode compliance — affordance + modal use semantic Fluent UI tokens, no hardcoded colors.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-18">Acceptance: "Browse Playbooks" affordance opens modal; modal lists every playbook + consumer mapping; clicking invokes through Path A.5 routing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple:
      1. Existing: PlaybookLibraryShell shared component already exists. Reuse without modification (or with minimal additive prop if affordance-host needs callback).
      2. Extension: this task adds a thin affordance + Dialog wrapper in the spaarke-ai code page. NO new shared component.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: spaarke-ai users have no in-flow path to browse + invoke any playbook outside the current conversation context; FR-18 acceptance criterion (≥3 consumer surfaces wired) not met.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">N/A — this is a Code Page task, not a BFF task. No publish-size check needed for BFF. (Code-page deploy bundle size is monitored separately by code-page-deploy skill.)</constraint>
    <constraint source="fluent-v9-component skill">Apply Fluent UI v9 patterns + Spaarke conventions (load skill before coding the affordance + Dialog wrapper).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>code-pages/spaarke-ai</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="PlaybookLibraryShell shared component" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx">
        Modal body — reuse with Dialog wrapper in the spaarke-ai code page.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Existing __tests__ pattern" location="src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/__tests__/">
        Test scaffold mirror.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 093 produced the audit recommending mount point(s) for the spaarke-ai chat surface.
      This task makes the wiring concrete. The Library modal already exists as a shared component;
      task 094-096 reuse it from 3 consumer surfaces. spaarke-ai is consumer surface 1 of 3.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="093" status="required">Audit doc at notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md — recommends mount point.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 092 (Wave 9) — adds the chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer; the Library modal "consumer mapping" column reads this table.</item>
      <item>Task 095 (next) — wires Library modal into Daily Briefing widget (consumer surface 2 of 3).</item>
      <item>Task 096 — wires Library modal into ad-hoc launcher (consumer surface 3 of 3).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in Code Page (.tsx file modification, tags code-page + ui, ADR-013+021 applicable, FR-18 acceptance criterion) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md (FR-18) + plan.md (Wave 9) + task 093 audit doc.
      Invoke the fluent-v9-component skill to load Fluent UI v9 patterns + Spaarke conventions.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependency">
      Confirm notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md exists. If not, STOP — task 093 must complete first.
      Confirm the audit's recommended mount point is unambiguous; if 2 candidates, pick the
      "ConversationPane toolbar / CommandHelpPanel" candidate (whichever is more in-flow).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read PlaybookLibraryShell contract">
      Re-confirm the modal body's props + callbacks per task 093 audit. Specifically: how does
      onPlaybookSelected fire? Does the Shell internally invoke through Path A.5, or does the host
      provide an invocation callback?
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Wire affordance at recommended mount point">
      Add a "Browse Playbooks" Button (Fluent UI v9 Button component, semantic tokens) at the
      recommended mount point. Wire onClick to open Dialog state. Use the existing app state
      management pattern (likely useState in the host component — do NOT introduce new state lib).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wrap PlaybookLibraryShell in Dialog">
      Use Fluent UI v9 Dialog / DialogSurface / DialogBody / DialogContent / DialogActions per
      Spaarke conventions. Mount PlaybookLibraryShell as the DialogContent body. Wire close
      on cancel + backdrop click. Pass any required props from the host (auth token, BFF base URL,
      etc. per the audit-confirmed contract).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire playbook-selected callback to Path A.5 invocation">
      When the modal fires onPlaybookSelected (or equivalent), the host invokes the selected playbook.
      Per task 093 audit:
      - If PlaybookLibraryShell already routes through Path A.5 internally, the host just closes the modal.
      - If the host owns invocation, call IInvokePlaybookAi via the spaarke-ai BFF surface (likely
        via authenticatedFetch + /api/ai/playbook/invoke or equivalent). MUST go through Path A.5;
        do NOT call AnalysisOrchestrationService directly.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="ADR-021 dark mode compliance">
      Verify affordance + Dialog use semantic tokens (tokens.colorNeutralBackground1, etc.).
      No hardcoded hex colors. Run dark-mode toggle smoke test in dev.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Component test">
      Create src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/__tests__/PlaybookLibraryAffordance.test.tsx
      (or place adjacent to host component if more natural). Test:
      - Affordance renders
      - Click opens Dialog (test by querying for PlaybookLibraryShell mock)
      - onPlaybookSelected callback fires with expected payload
      - Dialog closes on cancel
      Mock PlaybookLibraryShell as a thin stub (don't re-test its internals).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Build + test">
      Run: npm run build:prod (the production build per CLAUDE.md §12) in src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/
      Run: npm test for the new test file
      Goal: 0 errors; new test passes.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Manual smoke">
      Deploy the code page to spaarkedev1 dev via code-page-deploy skill (or document for owner to deploy).
      Manual smoke: open spaarke-ai chat → click "Browse Playbooks" → modal opens → modal lists
      playbooks WITH consumer mapping → click a playbook → invocation flows through Path A.5
      (verify by checking BFF logs for IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync invocation).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the new affordance code + test.
      Run `/adr-check` against ADR-013 + ADR-021 + spec FR-18.
      Fix any findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 094 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 095.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit">
      Commit affordance + Dialog wrapper + test with conventional message.
      Example: feat(spaarke-ai/r7): wire Playbook Library modal into chat surface (Wave 9 task 094, FR-18)
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (audit doc, shared component, host code-page files)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (add affordance + Dialog wrapper in host component)</tool>
    <tool>Write (component test file)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (npm run build:prod, npm test, git commit)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (fluent-v9-component for patterns)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (code-review at Step 9.5)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (adr-check at Step 9.5)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="modified-file">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/{host-component}.tsx (affordance + Dialog wrapper)</output>
    <output type="new-file">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/__tests__/PlaybookLibraryAffordance.test.tsx</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 095)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 094 ✅)</output>
    <output type="commit">feat(spaarke-ai/r7): wire Playbook Library modal into chat surface (Wave 9 task 094, FR-18)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>"Browse Playbooks" affordance mounted at the audit-recommended location in spaarke-ai chat surface</criterion>
    <criterion>Click opens a Dialog wrapping PlaybookLibraryShell (shared component reused without duplication)</criterion>
    <criterion>Modal lists every playbook with its consumer mapping visible per row</criterion>
    <criterion>Clicking a playbook invokes it through Path A.5 routing (verified via BFF log inspection during manual smoke)</criterion>
    <criterion>NO direct call to AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecuteAnalysisAsync from the launch path</criterion>
    <criterion>ADR-021 dark mode compliance — semantic tokens only, no hardcoded colors</criterion>
    <criterion>Component test passes — affordance renders + opens Dialog + callback fires</criterion>
    <criterion>npm run build:prod passes</criterion>
    <criterion>code-review + adr-check pass at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor)</criterion>
    <criterion>Manual smoke in spaarkedev1 dev confirms end-to-end flow</criterion>
    <criterion>Commit pushed to work/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
